	Length	254 bytes = the REAL practical max; first lookahead (?!(?:...){255,}) counts whole string - still valid
	Length	255 bytes: rejected by the regex's FIRST lookahead {255,} (NOT the 320 C check) - INVALID. Effective cap is 254, not 320.
	Length	320 bytes: even though the C pre-check allows <=320, the {255,} regex lookahead already rejects it - INVALID
	Length	321 bytes: rejected by the explicit C length pre-check (>320) BEFORE the regex runs - INVALID
